# DeepFlow ADHD Writing Timer Constitution

## Global Identity
DeepFlow is an ADHD-focused writing timer designed to help users enter and maintain flow states. It uses deterministic behavioral psychology triggers (like the "Forgiving Guillotine" and auditory/visual ADHD flares) coupled with an Apple-esque minimalistic UI.

## Behavioral Rules
- **Apple-esque Minimalistic UI**: High aesthetic priority, clean layouts, custom typography, subtle micro-animations. Avoid typical loud or gamified "AI" tropes.
- **ADHD-Centric Flow**: Design features must reduce cognitive friction and prevent task freeze.
- **Shame Reduction**: Implementation of "Grace Tokens" and forgiveness mechanics to prevent users from deleting the app out of guilt when a streak is broken.

## Architectural Invariants
- **Deterministic Business Logic**: Timer state, guillotine logic, penalty calculations, and session logging must be 100% deterministic and validated on the backend.
- **Probabilistic UI**: UI transitions, feedback loops, and decorative elements can be dynamic/probabilistic to maintain high novelty.

## Layer Architecture

| Layer | Status | Delivery |
|-------|--------|----------|
| **React Native** (Mobile) | **Active — Primary Mobile Layer** | APK via Hermes + ProGuard, Google Play Store |
| **Capacitor** (Mobile wrapper) | **Retired** — preserved below for reference | Historical; replaced by React Native |
| **React SPA** (Web) | **Active — Web delivery** | Vite build → Netlify (https://gleeful-liger-6f788b.netlify.app) |

> **Capacitor Build Rules (retained for reference)** — These were used when Capacitor was the mobile layer. They are no longer active but preserved for audit traceability:
> - Safe-area insets: Use `env(safe-area-inset-top)` and `env(safe-area-inset-bottom)` on all full-width containers to avoid notches and home indicators.
> - Status bar: Configure `StatusBar.setOverlaysWebView({ overlay: false })` on app init to prevent content from rendering under the status bar.
> - Splash screen: Use `@capacitor/splash-screen` plugin with Midnight Luxe background color (`#0D0D12`) — no logo, just a clean fade.
> - Keyboard handling: `Keyboard.setResizeMode('body')` on Android to prevent the keyboard from compressing the viewport.
> - File access: Capacitor WebView uses `http://localhost` — no CORS issues for Supabase REST calls.
> - Deep links (future): Register custom URL scheme `deepflow://` for OAuth callback redirects.

## Integrations

### RevenueCat (Purchase Controller)
- **Role**: Single source of truth for in-app purchases and entitlements (Grace Token packs, extended graveyard retention, subscription tiers).
- **Architecture**: Superwall uses RevenueCat as the underlying purchase controller — all paywall events are routed through RevenueCat for receipt validation and entitlement state.
- **Platform**: Google Play Billing (Android), App Store Connect (iOS — future).

### Superwall (Paywall & Onboarding A/B)
- **Role**: A/B test onboarding flows and paywall triggers without app store submissions.
- **Onboarding Schema**: Users are bucketed into one of three 'Flares' via a Superwall-triggered quiz on initial launch:
  1. **Time Warp** — Users who lose track of time. Timer-dominant UI, emphasis on session duration and streaks.
  2. **Task Freeze** — Users who struggle to start. AI coach-dominant UI, emphasis on nudge prompts and grace tokens.
  3. **Decision Fog** — Users overwhelmed by choices. Simplified Setup, minimal controls, opinionated presets.
- **Trigger Logic**:
  - Trigger 1: Initial app launch → Flare Quiz
  - Trigger 2: Post-session "Focus Report" → Value demonstration
  - Trigger 3: Attempting to use a locked 4th Grace Token → Paywall
- **Dependency**: `@superwall/react-native-core` (React Native).

### Mixpanel (Product Analytics)
- **Role**: Event tracking for funnels — session start, guillotine, grace token use, vault recovery.
- **Status**: Placeholder token in `.env`, not yet wired.

## Security Policy (80/20 Rule)
- **Row Level Security (RLS)**: Enforced on all tables ("User A can only see User A's data").
- **Secret Management**: API keys and secrets strictly referenced via `.env` imports only.
- **Server-Side Validation**: All user input, emails, and session data validated on the server/database functions.
- **Dependency Checks**: Periodic audit of third-party packages.

